{"rightSidebarLinks":[{"id":"textarea","title":"textarea","subLink":null},{"id":"example","title":"Example","subLink":[]},{"id":"specifyingrowsandcolsfortextarea","title":"Specifying rows and cols for textarea","subLink":[]},{"id":"specifyingmaxlengthandminlengthfortextarea","title":"Specifying maxlength and minlength for textarea","subLink":[]}],"title":"textarea","description":"","validatorType":"validators","validationTypeTitle":"Validators","type":"simple","category":"dynamic-forms","subCategory":"controls","linkTitle":"textarea","tabArray":{},"innerHtml":null,"htmlContent":"<div class=\"title-bar\"><p>To create a formControl of type textarea, you need to mention the formControl name and type in the <span class='highlighted'>serverData</span> and pass it in the <span class='highlighted'>formGroup</span> method of <span class='highlighted'>RxDynamicFormBuilder</span>.</p></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'example'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Example<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/textarea/validators#example'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-complete-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-complete-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-textarea-complete\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'specifyingrowsandcolsfortextarea'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Specifying rows and cols for textarea<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/textarea/validators#specifyingrowsandcolsfortextarea'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >If you want to specify rows and cols in textarea cotrol, then you can set <span class='highlighted'>rows</span> and <span class='highlighted'>cols</span> in the <span class='highlighted'>prop</span> property of <span class='highlighted'>additionalConfig</span> in the <span class='highlighted'>serverData</span>.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-size-component\"></div>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-size-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-textarea-size\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'specifyingmaxlengthandminlengthfortextarea'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Specifying maxlength and minlength for textarea<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/textarea/validators#specifyingmaxlengthandminlengthfortextarea'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >If you want to limit maxlength and minlength in textarea input, then you can set <span class='highlighted'>maxlength</span> and <span class='highlighted'>minlength</span> in the <span class='highlighted'>prop</span> property of <span class='highlighted'>additionalConfig</span> in the <span class='highlighted'>serverData</span>.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-inputlength-component\"></div>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"textarea-inputlength-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-textarea-inputlength\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n"}